paper: FingerTip 20K_ A Benchmark for Proactive and Personalized Mobile LLM Agents

differences.summary: Clarity score lowered due to added documentation mismatches
differences.why_impacts_score: More internal inconsistencies reduce clarity and reproducibility

evidence.baseline_quote: action-space naming inconsistencies and some missing protocol details hinder exact reproducibility.
evidence.final_quote: additional documentation mismatches (Section 4.3 references, Table 3 category count, CogAgent variant naming) hinder exact reproducibility.

differences.summary: Participant count/duration mismatch between Figure 3 and text
differences.why_impacts_score: Undermines trust in dataset scale and reporting accuracy

evidence.baseline_quote: Data collected from 91 users on their own Android phones, over 1–2 months.
evidence.final_quote: Figure 3 indicates “Users: 83” and “Time: 1month,” while text states 91 users.

differences.summary: CogAgent variant naming inconsistent across sections/tables/figures
differences.why_impacts_score: Confuses model comparability and hinders reproducibility of results

evidence.baseline_quote: GUI-control models (Aguvis-7B, CogAgent-9B, UI-TARS-1.5-7B) are compared.
evidence.final_quote: CogAgent variant naming is inconsistent—CogAgent-9B listed; Table 5 reports CogAgent-7B; Figure 6(b) labels CogAgent-9B.

differences.summary: Fine-tuning description vs Table 6 row mismatch (track-specific models vs single FT row)
differences.why_impacts_score: Reduces traceability of fine-tuned variants and confidence in reported gains

evidence.baseline_quote: LoRA fine-tuning of Qwen-2.5-VL-7B yields SR1 +6.6 and SR2 +11.0 (Table 6).
evidence.final_quote: Fine-tuning states two track-specific models, but Table 6 reports a single “Qwen-2.5-VL-7B-FT” row.

differences.summary: Validation split category count implausible (Val categories = 0 in Table 3)
differences.why_impacts_score: Raises doubts about dataset split coverage and documentation correctness

evidence.baseline_quote: The execution test set has 200 episodes (Table 3), risking sampling variance.
evidence.final_quote: Table 3 lists Val categories as 0, which is implausible and raises questions about split coverage.

differences.summary: SR1 values inconsistent between Table 4 and Figure 6(a) at O=0
differences.why_impacts_score: Inconsistent metrics presentation weakens confidence in performance claims

evidence.baseline_quote: Overall results are reported with O=0 (Table 4; Section 5.2).
evidence.final_quote: SR1 values at O=0 differ between Table 4 and Figure 6(a), without explanation.
